            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Symptoms: Ice buildup on indoor coil or refrigerant lines, reduced cooling, water leaks when ice melts\n\nCommon Causes:\n- Severely restricted airflow (dirty filter is #1 cause)\n- Low refrigerant due to leak\n- Blower fan failure\n- All return vents blocked or closed\n- Running AC when outdoor temperature is below 60°F\n\nDIY Steps:\n1. Turn off AC immediately\n2. Turn fan to ON (without cooling) to help melt ice\n3. Replace air filter\n4. Open all return vents\n5. Let ice melt completely (2-4 hours)\n6. Try running AC again\n\nCall a Professional If:\n- Freezing returns after thawing and filter replacement\n- Refrigerant leak suspected (hissing sound, oily residue)\n- Blower fan not working\n- Problem recurs repeatedly"
